newsitem.title: FRANCE: MATIF September wheat expires without delivery.
newsitem.headline: MATIF September wheat expires without delivery.

text.p: MATIF September wheat, the first month on the recently launched futures contract, expired without delivery, the French exchange confirmed on Thursday.
September open interest after Wednesday's last trading day was zero, a MATIF spokeswoman said.
No deliveries had been expected after a final two lots of September wheat changed hands on Wednesday.
During its seven-week life, the September contract traded a total of 129 50-tonne lots, or 6,450 tonnes.
Open interest peaked at 41 lots on July 22.
Traders said volume had been especially thin for September since most cash positions had been covered before the launch, which was delayed for legal reasons.
MATIF launched the wheat futures on July 5 but said earlier this month that slack physical markets had hampered trade.
